abstract: Backing the impeachment of President Trump is a politically risky step for many Democrats, more so given that Republicans have made clear the effort will die in the Senate.
snippet: Backing the impeachment of President Trump is a politically risky step for many Democrats, more so given that Republicans have made clear the effort will die in the Senate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats sent bills to the Senate only to watch them wither under dismissive Republican leadership on scores of occasions this year. They did so yet again on Wednesday, but this moment carried a weight all its own.

abstract: Every one of my colleagues has an obligation to pursue the truth, regardless of the politics.
snippet: Every one of my colleagues has an obligation to pursue the truth, regardless of the politics.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, the House of Representatives voted to impeach President Trump. That means that sometime early in the new year, I will take an oath on the Senate floor to uphold the Constitution, review evidence and follow the facts wherever they lead, regardless of party or ideology. Every one of my colleagues will be required to do the same.

abstract: President Donald Trump’s expansion of a program aimed at steering more veterans to private health care is getting an $8.9 billion boost as part of the massive government spending bill approved by the House, setting up a potential battle over the direction of the Veterans Affairs Department.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump’s expansion of a program aimed at steering more veterans to private health care is getting an $8.9 billion boost as part of the massive government spending bill approved by the House, setting up a potential battle over the direction of the Veterans Affairs Department.
headline_main: Budget Deal Advances VA Private Care Program Backed by Trump
headline_print_headline: Budget Deal Advances VA Private Care Program Backed by Trump

abstract: As he campaigns, Mr. Biden offers free-flowing analysis about the race he’s running in. Among his takes: He should be described as the front-runner, and he’s best positioned to beat President Trump.
snippet: As he campaigns, Mr. Biden offers free-flowing analysis about the race he’s running in. Among his takes: He should be described as the front-runner, and he’s best positioned to beat President Trump.
lead_paragraph: DECORAH, Iowa — Joseph R. Biden Jr. insists he is the front-runner in the Democratic primary race. He cites polling in battleground states. He suggests that his coattails would help down-ballot candidates win around the country. And he worries aloud about how his answer to a given question might play in the news media (“No matter how I answer that, I’m going to get clobbered,” he observed recently aboard his campaign bus).

abstract: The Trump administration will move forward with finalizing a rule on U.S. biofuel blending requirements for 2020 that is in line with a plan the Environmental Protection Agency unveiled in October, a White House spokesperson said on Wednesday.
snippet: The Trump administration will move forward with finalizing a rule on U.S. biofuel blending requirements for 2020 that is in line with a plan the Environmental Protection Agency unveiled in October, a White House spokesperson said on Wednesday.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — The Trump administration will move forward with finalizing a rule on U.S. biofuel blending requirements for 2020 that is in line with a plan the Environmental Protection Agency unveiled in October, a White House spokesperson said on Wednesday.
headline_main: Trump Administration to Move Ahead With Finalizing 2020 Biofuel Rule in Line With EPA Proposal: White House
headline_print_headline: Trump Administration to Move Ahead With Finalizing 2020 Biofuel Rule in Line With EPA Proposal: White House

abstract: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Wednesday that he would be happy to testify for a Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump if that would be required by law.
snippet: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Wednesday that he would be happy to testify for a Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump if that would be required by law.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said on Wednesday that he would be happy to testify for a Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump if that would be required by law.
headline_main: Pompeo: Will Cooperate With Impeachment Trial if Required by Law
headline_print_headline: Pompeo: Will Cooperate With Impeachment Trial if Required by Law
